    "Dr. Peter S. Ruckman": ", he says, \u201cBut the prince of the kingdom of Persia withstood me one and twenty days: but, lo, Michael, one of the chief princes, came to help me; and I remained there with the kings of Persia.\u201d He also says [v_Dan_10_20] in Daniel 10:20, \u201cNow will I return to fight with the prince of Persia: and when I am gone forth, lo, the prince of Grecia shall come.\u201d What you have in those verses is three sets of God-ordained rulers. There are demonic spiritual princes over the physical kingdoms of this world. These Satanic forces have been given \u201cthe [v_Luk_4_5] kingdoms of the world...and the glory of them\u201d(Luke 4:5\u20136) [v_Rom_7_14] because mankind is \u201csold under sin\u201d(Rom. 7:14). At the same time, there are spiritual beings who fight against the Devil\u2019s princes in order to influence the earthly kings and rulers for God. Michael the archangel is given by name. He is identified as [v_Dan_12_1] \u201cthe great prince\u201d of Israel (Dan. 12:1, 10:21). The unidentified [v_Dan_10_5] one in the passage is probably the Angel of the Lord (Dan. 10:5\u20136 [v_Rev_1_13] cf. Rev. 1:13\u201315). Finally, you have earthly rulers. Notice that one of \u201cthe kings [v_Dan_10_13] of Persia\u201d(Dan. 10:13) at that time was \u201cCyrus king of Persia\u201d [v_Dan_10_1] (Dan. 10:1). Here arises a paradox, for although Satan has been given control over the kingdoms of the earth, the purpose of earthly government should be to enforce the laws of God in society (Rom. 13:3\u20134). The Lord often carried out his purposes by earthly kings and rulers. Take Cyrus, for example. Over 200 years before Daniel 10, Isaiah `[char_Isaiah_Gen_26]` prophesied of Cyrus and called him God\u2019s \u201cshepherd\u201d (Isa. [v_Isa_45_1] 44:28) and the Lord\u2019s \u201canointed\u201d (Isa. 45:1). The Lord said He chose Cyrus to \u201cperform all my pleasure: even saying to Jerusalem, Thou shalt be built; and to the temple, Thy [v_Isa_44_28] foundation shall be laid\u201d (Isa. 44:28). In Isaiah `[char_Isaiah_Gen_26]` 45: 4, He said, \u201cFor Jacob `[char_Jacob_Ref]` my servant`s sake, and Israel mine elect, I have even called thee by thy name: I have surnamed thee, though thou hast not known me.\u201d So Cyrus `[char_Cyrus_Ref]` was a God-called minister for right, even though he belonged to the Devil\u2019s world system. That is why a struggle was occurring between the spiritual powers in Daniel\n13. But the problem with that argument, pragmatically, is that the Constitution, as the final standard of law in the United States, was overthrown in",
